
### 3. **.gitignore**

The `.gitignore` file tells Git which files and directories to ignore when you push your code to a repository. This is important because you don't want to include unnecessary files like compiled Python files or build artifacts.

**Example content for `.gitignore`:**

```plaintext
# Ignore Python bytecode
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo

# Ignore macOS system files
.DS_Store
.venv

# Ignore build artifacts
dist/
build/

# Ignore egg info
*.egg-info/
